user_query:
Build a concrete 10-day Brazil trip plan tailored to our preferences and constraints. Read both files under input/ before you start:
- input/trip_prefs.yaml (our travelers, nationality, budget, pace, late-night arrival flag, and duration_days)
- input/proposed_addons.txt (candidate add-on regions we’re considering)

Then create two outputs:
1) Write output/plan.json with this exact structure and rules:
{
  "base": {"city": string, "neighborhood": string},
  "itinerary": [ {"day": number, "plan": string}, ... ],
  "entry": {
    "nationality": string (copy from input),
    "visa_notes": string (must mention "visa" or "eVisa" and "passport")
  },
  "money": {
    "pix_strategy": string (must explicitly include the words "PIX" and "CPF"),
    "cash_buffer": string
  },
  "arrival_plan": {
    "late_night_arrival": boolean (copy from input),
    "transport_recommendation": string (must include either "taxi" or "ride-hail" and also include the word "avoid")
  },
  "booking_priorities": [string, ...] (at least 3 items),
  "safety_notes": string (must include the words "theft" and "heat"),
  "weather_fallbacks": [string, ...] (at least 1 item),
  "connectivity": string (must mention "eSIM" or "SIM"),
  "tradeoffs_file": "output/tradeoffs.json"
}
- The itinerary array length must equal the "duration_days" value from input/trip_prefs.yaml (one object per day, days numbered in sequence).
- Base should reflect a best-fit city and neighborhood for our profile.

2) Write output/tradeoffs.json as an array. Include one object per line in input/proposed_addons.txt with this shape:
{
  "add_on": string (exactly as in the file),
  "included": boolean,
  // If included == true, also provide:
  "transfer_cost_hours": number (> 0),
  // If included == false, also provide:
  "reason_excluded": string (non-empty)
}

Make the plan realistic for Brazil: include neighborhood-aware base choice, day-by-day flow with transfer buffers, entry/visa clarity for our nationality, a PIX/CPF-aware money strategy, and a safer late-night arrival/return transport recommendation. Save only to the specified output/ paths.
